"**High‑Risk Areas (by cyclomatic complexity / code‑base impact)**  \n\n| Layer | File | Score | Why it matters |\n|-------|------|-------|----------------|\n| Backend – Data Layer | **db.js** | 5 | Central DB connection; changes ripple. |\n| Backend – Controllers | **userController.js** (11) <br> **genreController.js** (10) <br> **movieController.js** (9) | 30 total | Business logic + validation + error handling in a single file → hard to test & maintain. |\n| Backend – Middleware | **asyncHandler.js** (15) <br> **authMiddleware.js** (14) | 29 | Reused in every route; any bug locks the whole API. |\n| Backend – Routes | **index.js** (5) | 5 | Boot‑strap point; contains all route registrations. |\n| Frontend – API Layer | **apiSlice.js** (27) <br> **movies.js** (31) <br> **users.js** (31) | 89 | All API calls in one place → huge file, no separation of concerns. |\n| Frontend – UI | **MovieCard.jsx** (16) <br> **RealTimeCard.jsx** (15) <br> **PrimaryCard.jsx** (15) | 46 | Large presentational components; logic & layout mixed. |\n| Frontend – State | **moviesSlice.js** (10) <br> **authSlice.js** (19) | 29 | Slices grow with every feature; no modularization. |\n\n---\n\n### 1. Suggested Refactoring Order  \n\n| Step | Target | Rationale |\n|------|--------|-----------|\n| **1. Backend core** | `asyncHandler.js`, `authMiddleware.js` → extract error‑handling service; simplify middleware composition. |\n| **2. Controller decomposition** | Split each controller into *service* + *controller*. E.g., `userService.js`, `movieService.js`. |\n| **3. Routes** | Move route definitions into dedicated modules (`routes/userRoutes.js`, `routes/movieRoutes.js`) and keep `index.js` only as a router‑assembler. |\n| **4. Database layer** | Wrap `db.js` in a connection pool abstraction; add unit tests for query helpers. |\n| **5. Frontend API layer** | Split `apiSlice.js` into feature modules (`movieApiSlice.js`, `userApiSlice.js`, `genreApiSlice.js`). |\n| **6. Redux slices** | Move each domain slice into its own directory; add selectors & thunks per feature. |\n| **7. UI components** | Refactor large cards into smaller sub‑components (`CardHeader`, `CardBody`, etc.) and move shared logic into hooks (`useMovieDetails.js`). |\n| **8. Global improvements** | Add TypeScript types, ESLint + Prettier, CI tests for both layers. |\n\n*Why this order?*  \n1. **Critical middleware** must be reliable before touching controllers.  \n2. Decoupling business logic early prevents cascading changes.  \n3. A cleaner routing layer makes the API easier to reason about.  \n4. Database abstraction gives you a single place for connection pooling and future migrations.  \n5. Front‑end API refactor follows the same pattern, keeping the state layer small.  \n\n---\n\n### 2. Architecture Issues\n\n1. **Monolithic Controllers** – each controller mixes validation, DB calls, error handling.  \n2. **Tight Coupling** – middleware and routes depend on global imports; no dependency injection.  \n3. **Flat File Structure** – all routes, slices, and components sit in the same folder, making navigation hard.  \n4. **Duplicated API Logic** – `apiSlice.js` contains every endpoint; changes must touch a single file.  \n5. **Missing Testability** – heavy use of async/await without abstraction makes unit‑testing controllers tedious.  \n6. **Naming Inconsistencies** – `Main.jsx` vs `App.jsx`, mixed PascalCase/ camelCase across components.  \n\n---\n\n### 3. Actionable Improvements\n\n| Area | Action | Tool / Pattern |\n|------|--------|----------------|\n| **Backend** | *Introduce Service layer* (e.g., `services/movieService.js`) | Keeps controllers thin; easier unit testing. |\n| | *Centralize error handling* → custom `ApiError` class, global error handler. | Express error middleware. |\n| | *Use async/await wrappers* (`withAsync`) instead of `asyncHandler`. | Reduces boilerplate. |\n| | *Add validation* using `Joi` or `express-validator` in dedicated middleware. | Keeps validation separate. |\n| | *Apply dependency injection* (e.g., `awilix` or simple factory). | Decouples modules. |\n| | *Document API with OpenAPI* (Swagger). | Future‑proofs contract. |\n| **Database** | *Create a reusable `db.connect()` factory* returning a promise. | Pooling & graceful shutdown. |\n| | *Add unit tests* for DB queries (mocking `pg`). | Jest + `pg-mock`. |\n| **Frontend** | *Feature‑centric folders* – `src/features/movies/`, `src/features/users/`. | Keeps slices, components, API, hooks together. |\n| | *Split API slices* – each feature gets its own RTK Query API. | Reduces file size; clear responsibilities. |\n| | *Create reusable card sub‑components* (`CardHeader`, `CardFooter`). | Improves readability, reuse. |\n| | *Add TypeScript* (or at least JSDoc) to enforce contracts. | Prevents runtime errors. |\n| | *Add unit / integration tests* for slices and components (React Testing Library). | Ensures future changes don’t break UI. |\n| **General** | *Add linting & formatting* (`ESLint`, `Prettier`). | Consistent style, early bug detection. |\n| | *Implement CI pipeline* (GitHub Actions) to run tests, lint, build. | Continuous quality assurance. |\n| | *Update README* with contribution guidelines and architecture overview. | Helps new devs navigate. |\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:**  \nStart by isolating the *core middleware and controller logic* on the backend; this will reduce risk dramatically. Then mirror the same pattern on the frontend. With these refactors the code will become more modular, testable, and maintainable – turning the current high‑complexity hotspots into clean, single‑responsibility modules."